Write a program to perform basic list operations, such as finding the length of a string list and calculating the maximum, minimum, and total sum of a numerical list.

SOLUTION:

list1=['Blue','Green','Yellow','Red','Pink','Orange']
list2=[21,11,9,17,27,5,3]
x=len(list1)
print "The size of list (colours) is",x
y=max(list2)
z=min(list2)
print "The maximum and minimum value in the list are",y, "and",z
a=sum(list2)
print "The sum of all elements in the list is",a
